FuncDef:
The qos low-latency enable command enables the low-latency function.
The undo qos low-latency enable command disables the low-latency function.
By default, the low-latency function is not enabled.
ExtraInfo:
Usage Scenario
To enable the low-latency function for flow queues in PQ scheduling mode, run the qos flow-queue low-latency enable command. After the low-latency function is globally disabled, the low-latency function that is enabled for a specified queue by running the queue command in the flow-queue profile is still effective.
Precautions
This command applies to the LPUF-480/LPUF-480-B/LPUI-480/LPUI-480-B/LPUI-480-L/LPUF-480-E/LPUI-480-CM/LPUI-200/LPUI-200-L/LPUF-200/LPUF-200-B/LPUI-1T/LPUI-1T-B/LPUI-1T-L/LPUI-1T-CM/LPUI-241/LPUI-241-B/LPUI-241-CM/LPUF-241/LPUF-241-E/LPUF-52.
